org.locationtech.geowave.core.index.simple

Class SimpleNumericIndexStrategy<T extends Number>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.locationtech.geowave.core.index.simple.SimpleNumericIndexStrategy<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IndexStrategy<MultiDimensionalNumericData,MultiDimensionalNumericData>, NumericIndexStrategy, PartitionIndexStrategy<MultiDimensionalNumericData,MultiDimensionalNumericData>, Persistable, SortedIndexStrategy<MultiDimensionalNumericData,MultiDimensionalNumericData>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    SimpleByteIndexStrategy, SimpleDoubleIndexStrategy, SimpleFloatIndexStrategy, SimpleIntegerIndexStrategy, SimpleLongIndexStrategy, SimpleShortIndexStrategy

    public abstract class SimpleNumericIndexStrategy<T extends Number>
extends Object
implements NumericIndexStrategy
    A simple 1-dimensional NumericIndexStrategy that represents an index of signed integer values (currently supports 16 bit, 32 bit, and 64 bit integers). The strategy doesn't use any binning. The ids are simply the byte arrays of the value. This index strategy will not perform well for inserting ranges because there will be too much replication of data.

      • getInsertionIds

        public InsertionIds getInsertionIds(MultiDimensionalNumericData indexedData)
        Returns all of the insertion ids for the range. Since this index strategy doensn't use binning, it will return the ByteArrayId of every value in the range (i.e. if you are storing a range using this index strategy, your data will be replicated for every integer value in the range).

        Returns a list of id's for insertion. The index strategy will use a reasonable default for the maximum duplication of insertion IDs

        Specified by:
